I thought in this post I would talk about something a little different than my usual content. Since the start of 2018 I have been posting a couple of times a month about new techniques I've been learning and different ideas I have for analysis of new data sets. However I haven't given much away about myself or how I came to have an interest in data science in the first place. This post is about my story of how my blog started and why am I passioned about data science.

&nbsp;

The purpose of this blog was to motivate me to carry on educating myself in data science techniques and to create a portfolio of my work to help my career in the future. I also wanted to create fun posts that were accessible to those at a more beginner level. From my research a lot of data science blogs currently out there are aimed at an expert audience. When reading them I often feel very stupid and inexperienced in comparison. I am sure I am no the only one who feels like this - therefore I wanted my blog to share my love of statistics and analysis with everyone especially those who are also just starting out or considering a job in data science or statistics.

The secret to how I have been teaching myself R programming.

&nbsp;

alternative title: The 5 best ways to learn new R techniques.
